cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the design of a multiuser MISO interference channel with energy harvesting, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and optimization. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes different solution approaches for the joint beamforming and power splitting problem, which involves mathematical programming and machine learning techniques, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well.
